text.__SUMMARY__: Quercus patelliformis is an Asian species of tree in the beech family. It is native to southern China (Guangdong, Guangxi, Hainan, Jiangxi).Quercus patelliformis is a tree up to 15 meters tall. Twigs are grayish brown. Leaves can be as much as 12 cm long.
